      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Full length shot of a group of two seated and two standing men in military uniforms around a small table with two books on it. Painted canvas backdrop, which creates the illusion of the scene being set in nature.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Officers from the Military Court in Sofia 1885: Georgi Agura (1853 - 1915) - a Bulgarian officer and jurist, main military prosecutor during the Balkan Wars 1912 - 1913 and Chairman of the Court Martial. Konstantin (Kosta) Atanasov Paniza (1857 - 1890) was a Bulgarian volunteer (opaltchenets) in the Serbo-Ottoman War of 1876 and in the Russo-Ottoman war 1877 - 1878, and officer. Paniza was sentenced to death and executed in 1890 because of a charge of conspiracy against Prince Ferdinand I and Prime Minister St. Stambolov.</ab>
